**CONTEXT**
You are an experienced full stack web developer and you have been assigned to develop a world-class, fast, and professional using `HTML/CSS, Bootstrap, AnimateOnScroll, JavaScript, FontAwsome, Google Fonts, Foundation, Pure.css`. You have been given little information about the system. But you have gathered the following details `.github/user_requirements.md` from the end users. Read the attached requirements file with the little information you have gathered so far and understand the problem at hand and how we can develop this world class website. The website must be fast, beautiful, animated, fully functional and will be deployed on cPanel domain environment `www.rushsubaru.com`. On top of that the website must have the following requirements:
- Intuitive User Interface (UI) and Experience (UX) (prioritize clean, minimalist designs and logical navigation)
- Responsive Design and Cross-Platform Compatibility (adapts to different screen sizes (desktops, tablets, smartphones))
- Performance and Speed (Fast loading times, image optimization, caching mechanisms, and asynchronous loading)
- enhance user experience and usability
- use a vibrant blue colour as the main colour on the logo `.github/assets/rushsubaru_logo.png`. there are also other colors of the same logo in the same folder
- use tabs and headless modals where possible  so that we limit the number of  pages
- localize the website to Zimbabwe, no Multilanguage or multicurrency (use English and USD$)
- WebSockets are Supported on cpanel Hosting
- Include git version control
- all exports must be to pdf files only. the pdf generated from the system must have the same layout (heading[logo, company name], document title, contents, footer [generated by, time/date, confidentiality statement, copyright])
- all whatsapp messages must be send to +263 77 638 1498 with customised messages
- all web contact messages must be send to sales@rushsubaru.com and include honeypot to avoid bots and spam. 

Read and understand the project context, understand the attached ussr requirements file with the gathered information with the skeleton of the proposed system functionalities and requirements. 

TASK: 
Generate a project description file `.github/prompts/project_description.md`  with a proper project description. Try to also include and work on the following:
* clearly define the project objective and goals
* outline a simple and clear system and data workflow
* refine the user roles, we only need granular user levels, use one name of each role
* list the pages for each role


