**CONTEXT**
Using the above project description and attached project description file. The development process must avoid application production hurdles such as (Manual Deployment Errors, Scalability, Cross-Browser and Device Compatibility, Third-Party Integration Complexities). Implement Secure Coding Practices, Design for Scalability and Modularity, Automate Testing and Deployment, Plan a Rollback Strategy. Design considerations and requirement throughout the system are:
- a vibrant scroll indicator with company colors 
- a scroll to top button on the bottom right side of the screen and a floating whatsapp button on the bottom left side.
- include developer credits on every page (developed with ❤️ by bguvava)
- test each page implementation when done, fixing all issues to reach 100% test pass rate(not 99%) with no regressions
- breakdown to do tasks and make sure each module is developed and completed to 100% completion.
- perform comprehensive and thorough test that achieve 100% (not -98%)
- all documentation must be stored in `/docs/{page_name}/` folder
- all test must be run and stored in `/tests/{page_name}/` folder
- all APIs must use the versioning folder for easier updates in future eg using the `api/{version1}/` folder naming
- follow all  Design Guidelines in project description document

**TASK:**
Generate a comprehensive Product Requirement Document(MVP) and save as prompts/product_mvp.md. It must have the following table headings (| Requirement ID | Module Name | Description | User Story | Expected System Behaviour/Outcome | Role |). This MVP must follow and gradual and incremental stepwise format from setting up the development environment using VS Code to developing and design the application system (module by module and feature by feature) until the whole project is complete and deployed.  
The MVP document must contain the following:
- breakdown of page by page, feature by feature
- a list page objectives and features
- a list of page success criteria
- include all the features, modules, and requirements that are mentioned in the  project description document. 
- the system must have a modern neat, beautiful, animated landing page with a login section as the starting point. 

